## 1. Introduction

In the present global scenario, it is very common to see people communicating with one another even 
if they speak different languages. But still, there is a huge difficulty in communicating with people 
because of the language barrier. So, to overcome this difficulty, the project "AI-Based Chat Language 
Translator" is developed.

This project is basically a command-line interface program using which the user can translate the text 
from one language to another. It is developed using the online translation service.

## 2. Objective

The main objectives of this project are as follows:

*   Develop a simple language translation system
*   Include support for many international and regional languages
*   Allow real-time text translation
*   Develop an easy-to-use command-line interface
*   Store the history of translated messages

## 3. Technologies Used

The technologies used to develop this project are as follows:
*   Programming Language: Python
*   Library: deep_translator
*   API: Google Translate using deep_translator library
*   Platform: Command Line Interface (CLI)

## 4. System Architecture

The working of the project can be explained with the help of the following steps:

1.  The user will be asked to input the text to be translated.
2.  Next, the user will be asked to select the language for translation.
3.  Then, the translation will take place.
4.  After translation, the translated message will be stored in the history.
5.  Finally, the translated message will be displayed to the user.
4. The translated text is shown to the user
5. The translation is stored in the history for later use

## 5. Features of the Project

The project offers a number of important features:
* It can support multiple languages like Hindi, English, French, etc.
* It can automatically detect languages.
* It can easily switch between source and target languages.
* It can store the translation history.
* It offers important commands like help, reset, swap, and history.
* It can handle errors like invalid languages.

## 6. Working of the Program

The program works in the following manner:
* The program starts and asks the user to input the source and target languages.
* The user can choose auto detection for the source language.
* The user can enter the text to be translated.
* The program uses Google Translator to get the translation.
* The translation is shown to the user.

The program offers a number of commands:
* help: It can display all the commands.
* lang: It can display all the languages.
* swap: It can swap the source and target languages.
* reset: It can reset the source and target languages.
* history: It can display the translation history.
* quit: It can quit the program.

